    "The fusion category is unitary if this bilinear form is positive definite, which follows from the reflection positivity of the underlying QFT.",
    "In particular, there exists a gauge (i.e.",
    "choice of basis in each trivalent junction vector space) such that the associator (equivalently F-symbols) is unitaryα ijk • (α ijk) † = ⊕ ℓ F ℓ ijk • (F ℓ ijk) † = id (L i ⊗L j)⊗L k, (2.9)where id L the canonical identity morphism associated to L ∈ C (physically this comes from the bulk identity operator restricted on the TDL L).",
    "In terms of the F-matrix, (2.9) is equivalent to,[F ℓ ijk] (p,α,β),(q,γ,δ) ([F ℓ ′ ijk] (q,γ,δ),(r,ϵ,ζ)) * = δ ℓℓ ′ δ pq δ αϵ δ βζ.",
    "(2.10)The above does not completely fix the gauge freedom of the F-matrix in general."
